          <p>I wanted to be different. </p>

          <p>So I set off to Vietnam, not knowing what it would give to me and I put my head down and worked. And worked. And worked some more. Along the way, however, I realized that no one should ever have to feel that way--desperate and without a plan, feeling constant overwhelmed. </p>

          </p>So I decided that I'd help people not have to.</p>.

          <p>With little money of our own and not a whole hell of a lot of business experience to start, we decided that we'd empower people with what we know: English and IELTS training. But not like other schools. The core of our business model starts with understanding that no one should have to suffer as we did. No one should have to "figure things out." Other schools may have more advanced equipment or more modern facilities, but you won't find a place that puts the concerns of their students abover everything else like we do. This is the heart of our business. </p>

